_localizedContents._text: AND WHY IS THERE A BODY ON MY BED!?
And when was I supposed to get there anyway?
More concerningly... who am I?

Uhm... where was I supposed to go, again?

{$Cohesion = 5}
Wow, I sure slept for a while. Time to get going!
Get up
This still grosses me out a bit, but upon closer inspection it seems to be subtly breathing. So it must be alive, I guess.
It seems to be lifeless... but it might as well just be asleep... I can't really tell without looking closely.
Approach the body
Look around the room

Whatever, the idea of touching that body is disturbing. What if it moved in response to me touching it? Gross! I'll just find the door and get out of here, I must have important things to do, I'm sure!
Ok, time to leave. I'll worry about whatever that thing is later.
Open the door
Oh, I forgot this room is actually pretty small... the door's right in front of me. How embarrassing...
M-MY HAND JUST WENT THROUGH THE HANDLE. SERIOUSLY, WHAT IS GOING ON TODAY.
I-it seems like it's not just the handle either... The same thing happens if I try to touch this shelf! Or this one!
Can I not touch anything at all!? AM I A GHOST!? DID I JUST DIE WITHOUT EVEN NOTICING THAT WOULD BE SO RIDICULOUS.

Ok, let me get a running start, just to make sure.
3... 2... 1... GO!
But surely if I'm a ghost I can at least go through the door, right?
Exit the room

OUCH!!! WHAT THE HELL, THAT HURT!

{$Cohesion = $Cohesion + 2}
How come I can't touch anything BUT the door?
But I guess that's good news. I think this proves I'm not a ghost, at least.
Still, I need to get out of here, I'm sure I'm supposed to have a very busy schedule today!
Maybe I should take a look at that body after all...
I should really buy a pair of glasses by the way. Now that I'm looking at the body this up-close, I can't really see its face properly. It just looks like a blurry mess.
Blurry vision aside, this body does seem to be vaguely familiar. Do I know them?
Could they know something about me?
Try waking them up
Let them be
Ok, let's just give this thing a little shake. I don't want to come across as rude.
I really don't think waking them up would be worth the risk. What if they got violent or something? I'll figure things out on my own.
Now, let's take a look around here. The door's over there, then there's the closet, then the m-
Mirror...
Look
Look away
My body... It's a fairly normal silhouette if I look at the whole thing, but as soon as I try focusing on an individual body part it's just a blurry, dark mess.
OH GOD IT GRABBED ME.
HEY! TAKE YOUR HAND OFF MY FACE! STOP TURNING MY HEAD AROUND!
I JUST WANNA LEAVE! WHY ARE YOU SO KEEN ON POINTING ME TOWARDS THE M-
It started moving a little. Does this mean they're waking up?
Mirror...
I-I don't have time for this, now do I? Let's just keep looking around.
What's with all this noise... did the body wake up after all?
The other body, the one that was asleep until a few moments ago, seems to be gently holding my head now...
But it also doesn't seem like it has any intention of letting me go.
I guess it just wants me to look...
